Notes: Pisces (Latin plural for "fish") is one of the constellations of the zodiac. Its brightest star is Eta Piscium. Deep-sky objects: M74 (a loosely-wound (type Sc) spiral galaxy), CL 0024+1654 (a massive galaxy cluster that lenses the galaxy behind it), CL0024+17 (ditto), & 3C 31 (an active galaxy and radio source in Perseus).
